As part of its plan to keep the business viable Anglo Gold Ashanti said it was considering retrenching as many as 8,500 miners. JOHANNESBURG - The National Union of Mineworkers (NUM) says it s working to avoid thousands of job losses at Anglo Gold Ashanti.Africa's biggest gold miner announced the restructuring of its South African businesses last month.As part of its plan to keep the business viable the mine said it was considering retrenching as many as 8,500 miners.(Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)